menu "breadboard: bb_mdns"

config BB_MDNS_AUTOREGISTER
    bool "Auto-init bb_mdns via bb_registry"
    default y
    help
        When enabled, bb_mdns self-initializes through bb_registry at
        bb_registry_init(server). Disable to skip the automatic init while
        keeping the component's public C API (caller must invoke bb_mdns_init manually).

config BB_MDNS_BROWSE_REFRESH_INTERVAL_S
    int "Periodic browse-refresh interval (seconds, 0 disables)"
    default 60
    range 0 3600
    help
        IDF's mDNS browser only fires the notify callback on PTR
        state changes (add / remove). Active advertisers re-announcing
        with the same TTL are silently refreshed in IDF's cache, so
        consumers never see a "still alive" event for stable peers and
        their last-seen timestamps stagnate.

        At this interval, bb_mdns deletes and re-creates each active
        browse subscription, forcing a fresh PTR scan. Any responder
        produces a fresh add notification; any peer that doesn't reply
        in the new query window fires its removal callback first.
        Set to 0 to disable the periodic refresh.

endmenu
